`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- North neighbor = `(chunkX, chunkZ - 1)` in grid convention (north = negative Z)
- Computing all 4 neighbors reuses the same `tempNoise`/`moistNoise` instances — they're cheap to create since only a single `.perlin()` sample is needed per chunk center
- Binary `biomeBlend[i] = 1` if biomes differ is simpler and more performant than a smooth value; the smooth gradient is achieved by the per-vertex proximity falloff in the renderer
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
