`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The no-seam guarantee is mathematical: both adjacent chunks blend `(colorA + colorB) / 2` at their shared boundary — because chunk A blends toward B's color at its east edge, and chunk B blends toward A's color at its west edge, using the same formula
- `computeBlendedColor` is exported as a pure function (zero dependencies) — this "testable seam" pattern lets 14 tests verify the blend math without any WebGL/R3F/mock setup
- The `sampleChunkBiome` private helper de-duplicates the noise-sample-per-chunk logic, allowing `generateChunkData` to evaluate 5 chunk centers (center + 4 neighbors) using shared `SeededNoise` instances in a single function call
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

